  div.row-fluid
    h2 Accuracy

    p Scientists know shockingly little about the details and composition of asteroids.  Visit the <a href="http://ssd.jpl.nasa.gov/sbdb.cgi">JPL's Small Body Database</a> and you will notice how sparse the information is.  This sort of information is public, meaning not even experts have the numbers they need to estimate the true value of an asteroid or the cost of mining it.

    p This scarcity of information is exactly why Planetary Resources is going to spend years or even decades investing in <a href="http://www.planetaryresources.com/technology/">LEO-telescopes and data-gathering flybys</a> before they ever touch an asteroid.  Although I tried hard to get as much accurate, up-to-date information as possible, everything on this site is a <em>very</em> rough estimation.

